knowledge_data.title: What is ANNR?
knowledge_data.description: AANR stands for Agriculture, Aquatic, and Natural Resources. It is a strategic sector that encompasses food production systems (crops, livestock, fisheries), natural resource management, biodiversity conservation, and climate-resilient innovations. In the Philippines, the AANR sector plays a crucial role in food security, rural development, and sustainable environmental stewardship.
